  "prompt": "How much money can I deposit in my account?",
  "response": "I don't have access to your personal bank account information, so I can't provide specific details about your deposit limits. However, deposit limits can vary based on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Type of Account**: Different accounts (e.g., checking, savings, money market) may have different deposit limits.\n2. **Bank Policies**: Each financial institution sets its own policies regarding deposit limits.\n3. **Regulatory Requirements**: Certain regulations may impose limits on the amount you can deposit, especially for large transactions.\n4. **Method of Deposit**: Limits can also depend on how you're depositing the money (e.g., cash, check, electronic transfer).\n\nTo find out the exact deposit limit for your account, I recommend:\n\n- **Contacting Your Bank Directly**: Speak with a representative who can provide detailed information tailored to your account.\n- **Reviewing Account Terms and Conditions**: These are often available on your bank's website or in the documentation you received when you opened the account.\n- **Using Online Banking Services**: Many banks offer detailed account information and FAQs through their online platforms.\n\nIf you're planning to deposit a large amount of money, it's also a good idea to inform your bank in advance to ensure a smooth transaction and to understand any potential reporting requirements.",
